text.tspan: “Belize is an independent and sovereign country located
on the north eastern coast of Central America. Belize is
bordered on the northwest by Mexico, on the east by
the Caribbean Sea, and on the south and west by
Guatemala. It has an area of 22,970 square kilometres
(8,867 sq mi) and a population of 387,879 (2017).[5] Its
mainland is about 180 mi (290 km) long and 68 mi (110
km) wide. It has the lowest population and population
